18 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Abuse, sexual abuse, or neglect of vulnerable adult -- penalties. (1)
19 Except as provided in subsection (3), a person who purposely or knowingly abuses, sexually abuses, or
20 neglects a vulnerable adult is guilty of a felony and shall be imprisoned for a term not to exceed 10 years and
21 be fined an amount not to exceed $10,000, or both.
22 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (3)(a), a person who negligently abuses a vulnerable adult
23 is, on a first conviction, guilty of a misdemeanor and shall be fined an amount not to exceed $1,000 or be
24 imprisoned in the county jail for a term not to exceed 1 year, or both.
25 (b) On a second or subsequent conviction of the conduct described in subsection (2)(a), the
26 person is guilty of a felony and shall be fined an amount not to exceed $10,000 or be imprisoned for a term not
27 to exceed 10 years, or both.
