10 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Failure to report abuse or neglect of vulnerable adult -- false
11 reporting -- penalties. A person is guilty of an offense and on conviction is punishable as provided in 46-18-
12 212 if the person purposely or knowingly:
13 (1) fails to make a report required by 52-3-811;
14 (2) fails to disclose the contents of a case record or report in violation of 52-3-813;
15 (3) gives false information to an adult protective services representative, or the county attorney, or
16 law enforcement officer with the purpose to implicate another person;
17 (4) reports to adult protective services, or the county attorney, or law enforcement authorities an
18 offense or other incident within the person's concern knowing that it did not occur; or
19 (5) pretends to furnish adult protective services, or the county attorney, or law enforcement
20 authorities with information relating to an offense or incident when the person knows that the person has no
21 information relating to the offense.
